{
  "message": "fix(hooks): background gt costs record in Stop hook to prevent SIGKILL\n\nThe Stop hook runs gt costs record which parses the full transcript file.\nOn large sessions this can take longer than the hook timeout, causing the\nprocess to be killed (signal 9). Backgrounding with & lets the hook return\nimmediately while costs recording completes independently.\n\nCloses: gt-kc7u\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
  "files": [
    {
      "sha": "f6195d6f5371d32eb9d51b199405108f0efe7cfa",
      "filename": "internal/hooks/config.go",
      "status": "modified",
      "additions": 1,
      "deletions": 1,
      "changes": 2,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/gastownhall/gastown/blob/4d35143f02ebbde05b1de7ad09b3e0acb10e1393/internal%2Fhooks%2Fconfig.go",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/gastownhall/gastown/raw/4d35143f02ebbde05b1de7ad09b3e0acb10e1393/internal%2Fhooks%2Fconfig.go",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/gastownhall/gastown/contents/internal%2Fhooks%2Fconfig.go?ref=4d35143f02ebbde05b1de7ad09b3e0acb10e1393",
      "patch": "@@ -797,7 +797,7 @@ func DefaultBase() *HooksConfig {\n \t\t\t\tHooks: []Hook{\n \t\t\t\t\t{\n \t\t\t\t\t\tType:    \"command\",\n-\t\t\t\t\t\tCommand: fmt.Sprintf(\"%s && gt costs record\", pathSetup),\n+\t\t\t\t\t\tCommand: fmt.Sprintf(\"%s && gt costs record &\", pathSetup),\n \t\t\t\t\t},\n \t\t\t\t},\n \t\t\t},"
    },
